import { useEffect, useState } from "react" import { useNavigate } from "react-router-dom" import "./BookingForm.css" export const BookingForm = () => { const [genres, setGenres] = useState([]) const [bookingForm, setBookingForm] = useState({ genreId: 0, startDate: "", endDate: "", numOfSongs: "", musicianRequest: false, sessionMusicians: false, photoRequest: false, videoRequest: false }) const navigate = useNavigate() const localFatBackUser = localStorage.getItem("fatback_user") const fatbackUserObject = JSON.parse(localFatBackUser) useEffect( () => { fetch(`http://localhost:8088/genres`) .then(response => response.json()) .then((genreArray) => { setGenres(genreArray) }) }, [] ) const submitButtonClick = (event) => { event.preventDefault() const requestFormToSendToAPI = { genreId: 0, startDate: bookingForm.startDate, endDate: bookingForm.endDate, numOfSongs: bookingForm.numOfSongs, musicianRequest: bookingForm.musicianRequest, sessionMusicians: bookingForm.sessionMusicians, photoRequest: bookingForm.photoRequest, videoRequest: bookingForm.videoRequest } return fetch(`http://localhost:8088/bookingRequest`, { method: "POST", headers: { "Cotent-Type": "application/json", }, body: JSON.stringify(requestFormToSendToAPI) }) .then(response => response.json()) .then(() => { navigate("/booking/myrequest") }) } return ( < div className="bookingForm" >
